{"type":"message","id":"3e8ca49c","parentId":"7e1144aa","timestamp":"2026-04-04T16:53:12.966Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I've read the GROUP.md file. Now I need to answer the user's question about scheduling messages on a particular day and time. \n\nFrom the context, I can see that:\n1. OpenClaw has cron jobs that run on specific schedules (good-morning, ai-news-digest, etc.)\n2. There are heartbeat mechanisms that can send messages periodically\n3. The system supports time-based scheduling\n\nFrom MEMORY.md I can see there's a cron system with 10 jobs that run at specific times.\n\nThe user is asking: \"Can u schedule the time for sending one msg for one particular day at particular time?\"\n\nThis is a yes/no question with an explanation. Based on my knowledge of OpenClaw:\n- Yes, OpenClaw can schedule messages using cron jobs\n- The cron system allows specifying exact times, days, and can run messages to specific channels/recipients\n- However, setting up a custom cron job might require accessing the system configuration\n\nI should answer in a friendly, helpful way as Nexa would — not overly formal, but clear. I should explain that yes, it's possible through cron jobs, and perhaps briefly mention how it works or that I can help set it up if needed.\n\nLet me check if there's any daily memory file that might have more context about recent scheduling issues.\n\nActually, for this simple question, I can answer directly based on my knowledge. I don't need to read more files unless the user asks for specific setup help.\n\nLet me craft a response that:\n1. Answers yes\n2. Explains briefly that cron jobs can schedule messages\n3. Offers to help set it up if they want\n4. Keeps the tone friendly and casual (Nexa's style)","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Yep! OpenClaw uses cron jobs for scheduled messages — that's how the good morning, word of the day, and other timed posts work already.\n\nTo 