{"type":"message","id":"f18b40d2","parentId":"b22392fb","timestamp":"2026-04-04T16:54:57.069Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"1021\",\n  \"reply_to_id\": \"1018\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"7924461837\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"Nrexya id:-1003606834639\",\n  \"sender\": \"Nemesis\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-04-04 16:54 UTC\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"Nrexya\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true,\n  \"was_mentioned\": true,\n  \"has_reply_context\": true\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Nemesis (7924461837)\",\n  \"id\": \"7924461837\",\n  \"name\": \"Nemesis\",\n  \"username\": \"nemesis0008\"\n}\n```\n\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n{\n  \"sender_label\": \"Nexaaa\",\n  \"body\": \"Yep! OpenClaw uses cron jobs for scheduled messages — that's how the good morning, word of the day, and other timed posts work already.\\n\\nTo schedule a custom one-time message, we'd add a new cron entry that runs at the specific date/time and sends to the group (or DM). The cron can be set for exact days and times.\\n\\nWant me to set something up? Tell me:\\n\\n• What message to send\\n• What day/time (in IST)\\n• Where to send it (this group, DM, etc.)\\n\\nI can configure it for you 💫\"\n}\n```\n\nu also have a reminder tool"}],"timestamp":1775321697061}}
