{"type":"message","id":"b71bef6a","parentId":"48f1c97b","timestamp":"2026-04-04T17:02:08.884Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to schedule a reminder with the good morning message on April 27th. I need to:\n\n1. Find out what the good morning message content is (it's already in the cron jobs, so I can check)\n2. Determine the exact time (they just said \"good morning mssg on 27th\" but didn't specify time)\n3. Confirm where to send it (likely the group, but should confirm)\n4. Schedule it using the cron tool\n\nLet me first check what the good morning message looks like by looking at the existing cron jobs configuration. I should read the memory/cron configuration or read the daily memory files to see what the good morning message says.\n\nActually, I should look at MEMORY.md and daily files to understand the cron setup better. But I know from the earlier reading that there's a \"good-morning\" cron job. I could also check the system cron or the OpenClaw configuration.\n\nBut let me be more efficient - I'll check if there's documentation or notes about what the good morning message contains. Looking at MEMORY.md, it lists cron jobs but doesn't show the actual message content. The good morning cron job is likely sending a generic good morning message.\n\nI should ask for the specific time they want on April 27th, and confirm it's for the group. I could also offer to customize the message if they want.\n\nLet me respond asking for the time and confirming the details.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Got it! I'll schedule the good morning message for April 27th. Just need to confirm:\n\n- **Time:** What IST time should it send? (The regular good morning is at 7 AM — want that same time?)\n- **Message:** Use the same template as the daily good morning, or customize it for April 27th?\n\nOnce you confirm, I'll set up the cron job 🖤"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"s