{"type":"message","id":"837a24ee","parentId":"cb406fdc","timestamp":"2026-04-04T17:12:23.930Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to send a sample resume first, then they'll provide their own details. I should create a sample resume PDF or just provide the text template so they can see the format before giving me their information.\n\nSince they mentioned she has a setup to convert text to PDF, I could either:\n1. Create a text template here and they can copy-paste it into their converter\n2. Actually create a PDF file in the workspace\n\nLet me just provide a clean, professional resume template in the chat as text first. That's the simplest and they can see the format before providing details.\n\nI'll use a standard modern resume format with sections: Contact, Summary, Experience, Education, Skills. I'll use placeholder names and content.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Sure thing! Here's a sample resume template (text version):\n\n```\nNEMESIS KUMAR\nEmail: nemesis@example.com | Phone: +91-XXXXXXXXXX\nLinkedIn: linkedin.com/in/nemesis | Location: Bhubaneswar, India\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\nResults-driven professional with 5+ years of experience in software development and team leadership. Proven track record of delivering scalable solutions and mentoring junior developers. Passionate about clean code, system architecture, and driving innovation.\n\nWORK EXPERIENCE\n\nSenior Software Engineer\nTechCorp Solutions | June 2020 – Present\n• Led a team of 6 developers in building microservices architecture serving 1M+ users\n• Improved system performance by 40% through optimization and caching strategies\n• Designed and implemented CI/CD pipelines reducing deployment time by 60%\n• Conducted code reviews and mentored junior engineers\n\nSoftware Developer\nInnovateTech | July 2018 – May 2020\n• Developed RESTful APIs using Node.js and Express, serving 500K+ requests daily\n• Implemented real-time features with WebSockets and Redis\n• Collaborated with cross-functional teams to deliver 15+ product features\n\nEDUCATION\n\nBachelor of Technology in Computer Science\nKIIT University | 2018\nCGPA: 8.2/10\n\nSKILLS\n\n• Languages: JavaScript, TypeScript, Python, Go\n• Frameworks: Node.js, React, Express, Next.js\n• Databases: PostgreSQL, MongoDB, Redis\n• DevOps: Docker, Kubernetes, AWS, GitHub Actions\n• Tools: Git, VS Code, Jira, Postman\n\nCERTIFICATIONS\n\n• AWS Certified Solutions Architect – Associate (2023)\n• MongoDB Certified Developer (2022)\n```\n\nReady when you are — send me your details and I'll generate the actual PDF file 🖤"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":21961,"output":730,"cacheRead":2816,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":25507,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775322735725,"responseId":"gen-1775322736-P4bEZbzhvLXYDKrkaAoy"}}
