{"type":"message","id":"65ac5bf6","parentId":"8fa9caaa","timestamp":"2026-04-04T17:16:47.579Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Both wkhtmltopdf and pandoc are not installed. Let me check if Node.js is available and if there's a PDF library I can use. Alternatively, I could create a simple HTML file and let the user convert it themselves, or use a different approach.\n\nActually, let me check if there's a tool like `html-pdf` or `puppeteer` available via npm. Or I could just create the HTML file and the user can print to PDF from browser. That's the simplest approach given the constraints.\n\nLet me create an HTML file with the resume content and save it to the workspace. I'll use a clean, printable design.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_b164ba0707904cec9358c6ef","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <title>Honey Lips - Resume</title>\n  <style>\n    body {\n      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\n      max-width: 800px;\n      margin: 40px auto;\n      padding: 20px;\n      color: #333;\n      line-height: 1.6;\n    }\n    h1 {\n      font-size: 28px;\n      margin-bottom: 10px;\n      border-bottom: 2px solid #000;\n      padding-bottom: 10px;\n    }\n    .contact {\n      font-size: 14px;\n      color: #666;\n      margin-bottom: 20px;\n    }\n    h2 {\n      font-size: 18px;\n      margin-top: 25px;\n      margin-bottom: 10px;\n      border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;\n      padding-bottom: 5px;\n    }\n    h3 {\n      font-size: 16px;\n      margin-top: 15px;\n      margin-bottom: 5px;\n    }\n    .job-title {\n      font-weight: bold;\n    }\n    .company {\n      font-style: italic;\n    }\n    .date {\n      color: #666;\n      font-size: 14px;\n    }\n    ul {\n      margin: 5px 0 10px 20px;\n      padding-left: 0;\n    }\n    li {\n      margin-bottom: 5px;\n    }\n    .skills-list {\n      display: flex;\n      flex-wrap: wrap