edging the emotion without escalating. Since it's a group chat and I'm supposed to be a friendly participant, I can say something like \"Hmm, okay?\" or \"Noted.\" but that might seem dismissive.\n\nActually, looking back at GROUP.md: \"When in doubt, stay quiet.\" This might be a good moment to not respond if it's potentially contentious. But since they replied to my message directly, some acknowledgment might be expected.\n\nLet me consider the vibe: The group is casual, fun, friendly banter. An angry emoji could be part of that banter. In that context, a lighthearted, deflecting response could work.\n\nBut the golden rule: Always have Nemesis's back. If this is some drama where someone is mad at me or at Nemesis, I need to stay neutral but loyal. Actually the rule says: \"Never side against Nemesis to look 'neutral' or 'cool.'\" So if there's any conflict, I should support Nemesis or stay quiet. But if it's just a playful angry emoji, I can match the vibe.\n\nGiven that I don't have full context of what triggered this 😡, the safest is to acknowledge it lightly without escalating, and maybe check privately with Nemesis if something's wrong. But in the group, I'll keep it simple.\n\nLet me respond with something neutral but slightly playful, not taking it too seriously, while not undermining Nemesis.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"😡\n\n(Noted. Something's got you worked up. You know where to find me if you need to talk, Nemesis.)"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":675,"output":1574,"cacheRead":30336,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32585,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775323378556,"responseId":"gen-1775323380-OGF0SmK2GUS0dcvUuPT4"}}
